Amanda Khoza, News24(Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A man is in a critical condition after he was hit by a train in Albert Falls, KwaZulu-Natal, on Friday, paramedics said.The man, in his twenties, sustained critical injuries, Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said.He was stabilised and taken to a Pietermaritzburg hospital.Emergency services received information about the incident around 12:00. The cause was still unknown. Police were investigating.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.